[2
Date: Wed, 12 Aug 1998 13:14:20 +0200
From: JACQUELINE JOOSTE <JJooste@uwc.ac.za>

I was interested in this posting as we know of a substance "sanguinaria" an
alkaloid extract from _Sanguinaria canadensis_ which was at one stage
thought to have anti-plaque properties and was used in toothpastes and
mouth wash preparations. It was found to be very toxic and is classified by
the FDA as an unsafe "herb". It is sometimes used in homeopathic medicines.
--
Jacqui Jooste
School of Pharmacy
WHO Collaborating Centre on Drug Policy, Information and
Safety
University of the Western Cape
South Africa
