[3
Date: Wed, 12 Aug 1998 08:26:38 +0100
From: Hugh de Glanville <hu@bjhc.demon.co.uk>

My 1987 edition of Manson's Tropical Medicine describes *sanguinarine* as a
poison found in the seeds of _Argemone mexicana_, the Mexican poppy, a
common weed in India often [fortuitously contaminating stocks of mustard
seed in India.
--
Hugh de Glanville
(retired ex-tropical MO)
e-mail: hu@bjhc.demon.co.uk
[This sounds to me a much more likely explanation than the N. American
bloodroot of the posts above - Mod.JW
