[4
Date: Wed, 12 Aug 1998 11:32:40 +0100 (BST)
From: D Stevenson <ds@holyrood.ed.ac.uk>

[This episode recalls the major outbreak of illness, with many deaths, in
Spain, about 20? years ago, eventually attributed to mustard oil (rape seed
oil) which had been prepared with a toxic additive, an industrial lubricant
for machinery. This had been sold as olive oil on the black market. Cases
appeared to have lung disease/atypical pneumonia. Careful epidemiology
found that the common factor for the victims was purchase of the black
market oil.
--
David Stevenson
University of Edinburgh
Scotland
e-mail: ds@holyrood.ed.ac.uk
